Perfect Vision is a real time video digitizer for the IBM PC.  With Perfect Vision, you can capture pictures off a VCR or video camera, and store them  an IBM-PC disk.  You can then load and edit the pictures in a paint program, or print them in a desktop publishing program.

Perfect Vision will capture a black and white image in 1/60 of a second or an interlaced image in 1/30 of a second.  This allows you to capture still pictures from a playing VCR, something previously available only on much more expensive equipment.

Resolution of captured pictures:

320 x 200 with 16 gray scales.
320 x 400 with 16 gray scales.

Hardware:

   Connects to printer port
   64K of on-board RAM
   Flash converter digitizes NTSC video in real time

Video Boards:

Perfect Vision supports the CGA, EGA, VGA, MCGA, and Hercules video adapter boards.  Refer to Appendix A for more on the different video adapter boards.


