There are currently a total of three file formats supported, PCX (PC Paintbrush), TIFF (which is a scanner format that is read by most desktop publishing programs), and RAW which is our own file format.  You can save aÇnÇdÇ load PCX pictures; this is extremely useful for saving the palette registers for later use and then loading PCX to restore them.  See appendix D for more information about pallette registers.

Please keep in mind that only the .RAW file format actually loads the image into internal buffers so that you can redisplay the picture in other video modes or change color registers around.  Loaded PCX pictures can be displayed but not modified, and TIFF cannot be reloaded.

For more information about the RAW disk format, please refer to appendix E.


